<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec_work" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Work</title>
	
    <p>
     One way to change the energy of an object is to do work on it.  Work is a change in energy that arises when an external force acts on an object that moves through some distance.
    </p>
		
	
	<definition>
	<title>Work</title>
	<statement>
	<p>The <term>work</term> done by a single force on an object is: <m>W = \int_i^f {\vec{F} \cdot d\vec{x}}</m>. </p>
	</statement>
	</definition>

	<exercises>
	<title>Exploring Work</title>

			<exercise>
			  <p>The definition of work can look pretty complicated the first time you see it!  Make a list of all the <em>symbols</em> you see in the equation.  For each symbol, write a short description of what you think that symbol means in the context of this equation.</p>
			</exercise>
			
		<p>
     Watch the video briefing below on work.
    </p>
		
