				<p>
     If you need a refresher on the dot product, see <xref ref="sec_dot-product"></xref>, especially the video: <xref ref="vec_vb-dot"></xref>.
    </p>
			
			<exercise>
			  <p>You are pulling a box across the floor using a horizontal rope with a tension force of 250 N.</p>
				
				<p>How much work (in J) have you done after the box has slid 3 m along the floor?</p>
			</exercise>
			<exercise>
			  <p>Suppose you were to angle your rope so that it makes an angle of <m>20^o</m> with the horizontal (the magnitude of the tension is unchanged).</p>
				
				<p>How much work (in J) have you done after the box has slid 3 m along the floor?</p>
			</exercise>
			<exercise>
				<p>Why is the work you calculated for the two situations above not the same?</p>
			</exercise>
			
		</exercises>
	
